parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The passenger airbag warning light illuminates
and the vehicle is deemed unsafe to operate with a passenger in the front seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint defects can lead to peeling, flaking, and corrosion, which can compromise the vehicle's appearance and structural integrity. The recall issues can cause frustration and inconvenience for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Peeling paint
flaking paint
corrosion
delayed or denied recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frame rust and corrosion can lead to structural weaknesses, compromising the vehicle's safety and performance. In severe cases, it can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Rust holes
weak spots
corrosion
frame damage
rusted-off components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lift Gate and Foot Step Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lift gate and foot step issues can cause accidents or injuries, particularly when the lift gate opens or closes unexpectedly or when passengers fall while using the foot step.
symptoms: Lift gate opens or closes unexpectedly
foot step is too narrow
insufficient surface for proper footing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floorboard, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or has reduced braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to feel loose or rattle, and may result in a hissing sound when the brakes are applied, which can lead to a loss of braking power and increased stopping distance.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels loose or rattles
a hissing sound is heard when the brakes are applied
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake dust interference can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, and may result in a reduced braking power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window rubber sealing can cause water to enter the vehicle's body and doors, which can lead to electrical fires or interfere with the computer operating system, affecting the vehicle's driving ability.
symptoms: Water enters the vehicle's body and doors
electrical components in the doors are exposed to water
the window rubber sealing is curled up or fallen off.
